~ parameters: two syntaxes — pipes and parens.
~ flags use a trailing ! on the final word before the closing delimiter.


~ ── three forms ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
~
~   |value|               positional — single word, no !
~   |key value|           named — first word is key, rest is value
~   |key - value|         named — hyphen when the key itself is multi-word
~   |flag!|               boolean — trailing ! marks presence
~   |multi word flag!|    boolean — trailing ! works for any length


~ ── positional ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@figure
|lamp.png|
|caption The second-order Fresnel lens|
figure@


~ ── named ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

~ first word is key, rest is value — no hyphen needed for single-word keys

@scene |mood calm| |location harbour|
The harbour was still.
scene@

~ hyphen escape for multi-word keys

@panel |background colour - dark slate|
The lantern room was unlit.
panel@


~ ── flags ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

~ trailing ! — unambiguous regardless of word count
~ ! mid-value is just punctuation; only the final ! before | counts

@figure
|full width!|
|lamp.png|
|caption The second-order Fresnel lens|
figure@

|dark mode!|
|published!|
|allow line breaks!|

~ mid-value ! is safe — not a flag

|caption Wow! What a lens|


~ ── parens — self-closing, params at the open ───────────────────────────────────
~
~ parens always mean no body. comma-separated. same three forms apply inside.

@badge(tone good, verified!)
@figure(src lamp.png, caption The second-order Fresnel lens, full width!)
@watermark(draft!, label Do not distribute)

~ with body: use open/close and pipes instead

@figure
|src lamp.png|
|caption The second-order Fresnel lens|
|full width!|
Some additional context about this particular lens.
figure@


~ ── pipes scatter, last one wins ────────────────────────────────────────────────

@scene
|mood calm|
The harbour was still.
|mood tense|
Then the bell began to ring.
scene@
